I'm now in the 'Source' directory of the 'cloud-to-butt' Chrome extension repository. This directory contains the source code files for the extension. I can see two files listed:

1. content_script.js - This likely contains the main functionality of the extension that replaces text on webpages.
2. manifest.json - This is the configuration file that all Chrome extensions require.

To view the actual code implementation, I should first examine the content_script.js file since it would contain the logic that performs the text replacement functionality (replacing 'the cloud' with 'my butt').
